summary: Have You Kissed Your Favourite Genius Today?  Let’s Stony like it’s 2012! This was a sketch I drew a while after Civil War...
caption:
Have You Kissed Your Favourite Genius Today?

Let’s Stony like it’s 2012!

This was a sketch I drew a while after Civil War (let’s call it therapy) but I have faced the fact that I’m never going to finish it. Not aside from cleaning it up some and slapping on some flat colours. So yeah. Here we are. I hope you enjoy some old-fashioned Stony!

title: Peter Parker's Fantastic Field Trip
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2DnjWtw

by Anonymous

Peter Parker didn’t think his day could get any worse- until he was proven wrong. When his teacher announces that his class is taking a field trip to Stark Industries, Peter knows that there’s no getting out of this. Tony’s gonna embarrass him, Cap’s gonna give his annoying ‘don’t do drugs’ lecture, and there’s no telling what the rest of the Avengers will do.

Basically the old Field Trip trope that I wanted to try.

body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2I7Bx7x

by once_and_future

“Take me out to the ball game, take me out with the crowd,” Steve sings, his shoulder bumping into Tony’s as he sways back and forth. “Come on, Tony, sing!”

“I am a genius billionaire playboy philanthropist,” Tony protests around a mouthful of hot dog. “I do not sing.”

Or, Steve and Tony go to a ball game. It all kind of snowballs from there.

summary: ‪What if Tony Stark lies wide awake because there are nights he remembers the blocks and blocks of concrete falling on top of...
body: ‪What if Tony Stark lies wide awake because there are nights he remembers the blocks and blocks of concrete falling on top of him and blacking out in the waters gasping for air when his Malibu home was destroyed. What if he is afraid to close his eyes because he’s afraid that if he opens his eyes he’ll be in Tennessee again, surrounded by snow having to find means to survive on his own with nothing but his bare hands, again. What if he holds Pepper whose sleeping besides him a little tighter every night because he knows he’ll have to live with the guilt that one day again she will not know where Tony is once he’s off on another mission, and neither will he have the means to be able to tell her he’s okay.
